Historias Reais- Privacy Policy


Last updated: 21 March 2026


1. Overview

This Privacy Policy explains how CanalStoryBR ("I", "me") handles information in

connection with the tools and automations used to publish my own storytelling

videos to social platforms such as TikTok, Instagram, and YouTube.


2. What data I collect

The Service is designed only to publish content on my own accounts. It does not

provide registration or login for other users, and it does not intentionally collect

personal data directly from visitors.


The only information that may be processed indirectly comes from:

- the social platforms where I publish (for example, TikTok showing comments,

  likes, or aggregated analytics);

- the technical data those platforms expose through their official APIs

  (for example, video IDs, publish status, or basic performance metrics).


3. How I use the data

Any data accessed via official APIs is used only for:

- publishing my videos (uploading files, setting captions and privacy settings);

- verifying whether a post was published successfully;

- optionally checking basic performance indicators such as views or likes.


I do not sell, rent, or trade personal data. I do not use this data to build user

profiles outside what is already provided by the platforms themselves.


4. Data sharing

I do not share data from the Service with third parties, except:

- the social platforms themselves (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.), which already

  process your data under their own terms and privacy policies;

- service providers that I may use for infrastructure (for example, cloud storage

  or hosting), who are bound by their own privacy and security obligations.


5. Cookies and tracking

The automation tools I use to publish content may run on my own machines or in

cloud environments. They are not designed as public-facing websites with cookies.

If you interact with my content on third-party platforms, those platforms may use

cookies and tracking technologies according to their own policies.


6. Data retention

I retain only what is necessary to keep the publishing workflow working, such as:

- logs of successful or failed publications;

- IDs of posts;

- timestamps of publishing.


I do not intentionally store or export personal data about viewers or followers

outside of what is already available in the platform dashboards.


7. Your rights

Any personal data associated with your use of TikTok, Instagram, YouTube or other

platforms is controlled primarily by those platforms. To exercise access, deletion,

or correction rights, you should use the tools provided by each platform or contact

them directly.


8. Security

I take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect the systems I

control (for example, not sharing API keys and restricting access). However, no

system is 100% secure, and I cannot guarantee absolute security.


9. Changes to this Privacy Policy

I may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the

top of this page shows the latest version. Continued use of the Service after any

changes means you accept the updated policy.


